x4freetext: Pd-300 Neutron Generator
The deuteron beam energy is 136 keV and beam
current is 260 uA.
Three Eu2O3 samples (99.99%
pure) were compressed at 10 t/cm2 to obtain 2.0 cm in
diameter. Thickness was 0.1427, 0.1718, and 0.1065 cm.
Each one of them was sandwiched between two Nb monitor
foils (Nb, 99.99% pure, 0.5 mm thick) of the same
diameter as the samples.
It consisted of a relative efficiency of
around 68% and an energy resolution of 1.69 keV at
1332 keV for Co-60 HPGe detector (ORTEC, model GEM 60P,
crystal diameter: 70.1 mm, crystal length: 72.3 mm,
made in USA). The efficiency of the detector was
pre-calibrated using various standard gamma sources,
which were Co-57, Co-60, Cd-109, Ba-133, Cs-137,
The Au-Si surface barrier detector used to
detect alphas from d-T reaction in alpha-particle
tube was positioned at 135 deg and 110 cm from the
target.
The irradiation was lasted approximately 120
min with a yield of 3 to 4E10 n/(4pi*s). The groups
of samples were positioned at 0, 90, and 135 deg
relative to the deuteron beam direction and centered
about the T-Ti target at distances of 40 mm. To avoid
the effect of low energy neutrons, samples were
wrapped in cadmium foil. During irradiation, the
neutron flux was monitored by accompanying
alpha-particles so that corrections could be made for
small variations in the yield.
Total correction factor of the activity: F=fs*fg*fc.
fs was correction factors for the self-absorption of
the sample, fg was correction factors for the
counting geometry, fc was correction factors for the
coincidence sum effect of the cascading gamma rays.
Correction factors for the self-absorption at 89.489,
for sample 3 (0.1065 cm thick).
Total uncertainty
Counting statistics 0.2-3.3%
Detector efficiency 2-4.5%
Self-absorption of gamma-rays 1%
Cooling and measuring times 0.1-0.2%
Branching ratio of the
characteristic gamma-rays 0.8-11.3%
Half-life of the radioactive product
nuclei 0.1-1.1%
Weight of the samples 0.1%
Abundance of the target isotope 0.2%
Standard cross sections uncertainties 1.5%
